<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 02 at 3:18PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A snow squall will affect east central Broadwater, southeastern
Meagher and north central Gallatin Counties through 400 PM MDT...
At 315 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a snow squall over Deep
Creek Pass on Highway 12, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Snow squall, with visibility below one quarter of a
mile. Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...A period of heavy snow and poor visibility will affect
travelers along Highway 12 from Townsend to White Sulphur
Springs.
Locations impacted include...
White Sulphur Springs, Lennep and Ringling.
This includes the following highways...
Highway 12 between mile markers 3 and 67.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Drive with caution if you must drive through the snow squall.</instruction>
